animal.description:
Meet Spicy! He has been raised in foster care and is well socialized with kids and dogs. He is estimated to be a large dog when full grown (somewhere between 60-80 lbs) and will do best in a home that has a yard, experience with large/powerful breeds, and willingness to work on training and exposures throughout puppyhood and his transition into adult life. Spicy can be a bit reserved at times (he's slowly becoming more adventurous) so he needs someone who will patiently help him come out of his shell. 

His $400 adoption fee covers his vaccinations, deworming, microchip, neuter, collar, and leash. $100 will be refunded upon completion of any puppy training program. Please complete an adoption application at dogsfurdays.org to set up a virtual meet and greet!

animal.description:
GIMMEL is affectionate and playful. He loves to cuddle with humans and play with dogs. He's good with cats too.  He is sometimes talkative when he wants you to pet him. He's happy to play in the yard with a buddy or lay with you on the couch for a nap - he's a versatile happy puppy. Cuddle bug teddy bear type.

The litter is an interesting assortment of colors and patterns. Mom appears to be mostly Lab. At this age, they change appearance by the week so we don't know what he may be mixed with - so far it seems to be Lab mixed with either Heeler, Beagle, Hound or Cur mixed in - all great breeds :-) We think he'll be a large dog.

His adoption fee includes his neutering, vaccine series, rabies, deworming, and microchip. He was born on a reservation we work with October 21, 2020.  

** Do you live in our adopting area? ** Do you have another young playful friendly dog of similar adult breed size? ** IF YES to these questions, then please proceed with the application process below! :-)

We have specific ADOPTION and COVID rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy. 

First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application to see if the pet is still available. (Please do not call or text). We'll send you a link to the application.

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal. If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this. 

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you. 

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets. 

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets. At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we), keep to a properly distanced social distance and have hand sanitizer and your own leash.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. No young children for our adoptions please. Puppies MUST adopt to families that have another young friendly playful dog of similar breed size when grown. 

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos  etc will make our work worthwhile :-))

Our volunteers and adoption board are working diligently with an overload of inquiries since Covid to match families and forever pets. Our workload on the reservations has also increased. We're sorry, but if you email us with questions that are already answered here or fill out an application that does not fit the parameters of our procedures we will not be able to reply to you. Thank you for your understanding on this!

Thank you - we look forward to hearing from you and having another furbaby united with a furever family!

animal.description:
Meet Riley. His owner passed away last month. A lovely family took him in but the children in the family make him nervous so he is in search of an adult only home.~ Riley is smart and very well trained. very well trained. He loves to play fetch especially with a frisbee, and likes to play with his toys. You can put a treat on the ground and ask him to wait, he won't take it until told, take it". He knows all the basic one/two word commands sit, stay, wait, down, lay down, leave it (but normally leaves it anyway) lol, shake (paw) and other one/paw. He gets lost in his reflection in mirrors and shiny surfaces. If you ask him "where is he?", he goes looking for himself and then barks at himself, lol! It is adorable! He is a watch dog, he will bark if he here's a knock at the door or someone enter the door, He will shower you with kisses and cuddles. He is not crate trained but there is no need, that I found. He is a good jumper and he loves to go for rides in the car.

Riley is around 5.5 years old and 55-60 lbs.

Please email us at AlmostHome4Dogs@yahoo.com to find out if Riley is the right one for you! (Local adoptions preferred - Philadelphia and tri-state area [South Jersey and northern Delaware] only.)

PLEASE READ BEFORE CONTACTING US!
We are NOT a shelter: All of our dogs live in private homes with foster families. Come and meet the Almost Home dogs and their fosters at our Meet & Greet events, where you can learn more about our wonderful dogs from the people who live with them, find out which dogs are on their way and when they'll arrive, and fill out an application to adopt or foster.

We cannot adopt to homes where electric-shock fencing systems or training collars are used. For more information on the dangers of electric-shock collars, please visit banshockcollars.ca/studies.php and http://www.hollysden.com/say_no_to_shock.htm (scroll down and click on the "Invisible Fencing Systems" link).

We do not have an online adoption application; to request an application, e-mail us at AlmostHome4Dogs@yahoo.com. To speed e-mail processing time, be sure to note the name of the dog you are inquiring about in the Subject line. For Meet & Greet times and locations, visit our home page, where you also will find information on our adoption process and fees.

FOSTER FAMILIES ARE LIFESAVERS!! Can you open your heart and home for a few weeks to homeless shelter dog? Remember, by fostering a dog, you save TWO lives - that of your foster dog, and that of the dog who takes his place in the shelter! Come to a Meet & Greet and find out if fostering is for you - there's no reward quite like the feeling that you've saved a life ... or two!

animal.description:
Howdy! I'm Tyson, a very friendly 3-year-old Catahoula Hound Dog mix. I was recently returned to MaxFund because my owners didn't have enough time to meet my needs, and because of that I developed some anxiety.
I will definitely need some crate and basic training with my new family. We also think I would be a great agility dog! Agility training would help keep me mentally stimulated, as well as provide plenty of exercise for me. Because I'm a hound dog, 
I need plenty of room to run around and plenty of activities - if I get bored you will hear the infamous Hound Howl. While having a yard is not always a requirement, in this situation 

I would need to go to a family with a yard. I do great with kiddos, but not so great with cats. Due to my current anxiety, I want to go to a one doggo household, at least until I get some more training and work on some of my anxiety. Do you have the time to teach me how to be a first-rate canine citizen? Will you provide me with an active lifestyle and training so I don't get bored? Will you love me furever and ever? Call the folks at MaxFund to set up an appointment to meet me! 303-595-4917

MaxFund is a physical shelter located at 1005 Galapago St in Denver, Colorado.
If you are interested in learning more about a dog, please call 303-595-4917 to make an appointment
.
This PetFinder account is managed by volunteers, and the most up-to-date information is at the shelter.
How our adoption process works:
1. You MUST come into the shelter to meet a dog you are interested in (and meet a few others, while you’re at it!)
                      Our hours are 10-5 Mon, Wed, Thu Fri / 11-5 Saturday / 12-5 Sunday
                We suggest you call ahead to be sure the dog(s) do not have pending applications
2. You will fill out your adoption application, including references, after finding a dog you’d like to adopt
3. The application review and reference checks will take up to 3-5 business days; you will not be able to bring a dog home same-day
                We only take 2 applications per dog, before they are unavailable. This is why we suggest you call ahead to check the status of the pup!
 
We do not adopt out-of-state.
Thank you for choosing to rescue!

animal.description:
PLEASE DO NOT ASK ABOUT AVAILABILITY OR EMAIL THROUGH PETFINDER or ADOPT-A-PET - WE CANNOT RESPOND - READ THE PROCESS BELOW.

If you're interested in any of our wonderful dogs, you must FIRST fill out an Adoption Application at our website listed below. Once we receive it, we'll forward it to the foster family for follow up. We are 100% foster based, so we don't have a facility. Review the process FAQ at our website.

Adoption applications can be found here: http://labrescuefresno.org/available-labs/adoption-application/

Adoption Fees Adult Dog (10 mos. - 7 years): $250.00 Puppy (9 mos. and under): $350.00 Senior (8 yrs. and up)/Special Needs Dog: $100.00

Ace - Black Male Mix, 8 years old, 90 lbs
Sometimes you need an Ace up your sleeve. Thank goodness I did. I had a home and was cared for (you don't get my size without a little love). Then I found myself in a shelter where I played my best cards, and wouldn't you know it - jackpot. The defenders of dogs swept in and rescued me, paid for surgeries to remove the growth on my eye, clean my teeth, and we won't mention the other surgery, let's just say my bark is an octave higher now.
I'm eight years old but still enjoy my daily walks. After a good walk, I love to lay at my foster dad's feet, under his desk, behind his chair, anywhere where he will notice how lucky he is to have me. I even go into my crate just to give him some room. When I want to go outside, I just go through the two doggie doors and I have the backyard to explore. I'm wicked smart, I learned those doors less than an hour after being rescued. I've learned a few commands too, and if you want to teach me more, I'm game. I love to show how smart I am.
I really am a friendly dude who loves people and dogs of all shapes and sizes. My foster dad says I'm cat friendly but this cat has seen lots of fosters and thinks this is his house! I'll take his word. I am super smart but have never been to school - a diamond in the rough, waiting for you to teach me the ropes - but the hard parts are done! I'm potty and crate trained and know not to chew your things. I love walks and laying by your feet.
Ace is available for adoption through the Labrador Retriever Rescue of Fresno. He is a very sweet boy who is happy, loving and just wants to please and be loved. Ace is an ideal family dog and would be a great addition to a family with children or with a retired family. He is housetrained and is learning basic commands. He is a great walking companion, and beyond that, just wants to be with his human friends. He loves his doggy friends and people of all shapes and sizes. If you have room in your heart and your home for this super sweet winner, put your cards on the table (including the Aces up your sleeve) and fill out an application at our website www.LabRescueFresno.Org.
If you have already submitted an application for another LRRF dog, simply hit reply to whomever answered your original application and ask to have it forwarded to Ace!!
If you are interested in adopting through Labrador Retriever Rescue of Fresno, you must first fill out an Adoption Application located at our website www.LabRescueFresno.org All dogs are spayed/neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines including rabies; flea/tick topical drops, heartworm tested and microchipped. Thank you for opting to adopt!!
Adoption FeesAdult Dog (10 mos. - 7 years): $250.00 Puppy (9 mos. and under): $350.00Senior (8 yrs. and up)/Special Needs Dog: $100.00

animal.description:
Clash is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Clash is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~2 years
Weight: ~45lbs
Housebroken: Yes
Crate trained: Working on it! Takes time to settle, but overall doing well with his crate-training.
Dog sociability: Frustrated greeter on leash and may bark/pull/lunge at other dogs in an effort to meet them.
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Unknown, but he can be mouthy (play bites) so only recommended for older kids/teenagers
Ideal home: An active home in a quieter neighborhood ready and willing to work on training! He is not a match for an elevator building due to his leash frustration.

Clash is a dashingly handsome and sweet guy! He is so much fun and will keep you busy. Once he's got some some playtime in, he is happy to cuddle up next to you for a snooze. Clash has been working on his tricks and can 'sit', 'stay', 'lie down', and is working on 'shake'! He has not had any accidents in the house with regular walking. He goes to his "room" (crate) easily for meals and with the reward of a pumpkin kong or puzzle toy. He often put's himself to bed at night and after long walks. Occasionally goes to his crate to lay down on his own. Overall, he will benefit from an active adopter that can continue to work on training and provide this goofball with lots of good mental and physical enrichment.

Clash's adoption fee is 300. He is neutered, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. 

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

Not sure what your favorite day of the week is? After meeting this adorable guy named Friday, you’ll be convinced Fridays (both the dog and the day) are truly the best! 

This sweet boy is arriving this SATURDAY, January 30th, from San Antonio and will be looking for a foster or foster-to-adopt situation. 

Poor Friday was found emaciated and running around on a ranch in South Texas, so he is definitely ready for a new start with lots of love! Despite his sad start, Friday is VERY sweet and friendly! His gorgeous short coat comes from his Blue Lacy mix. Friday is about 5 years old and 85 pounds. He does well with people of all ages and other dogs! He would do best in a home WITHOUT cats or small animals due to his hunting instincts. Friday will need CONSISTENCY with housebreaking as he has been living in an outdoor pen with an animal rescue in South Texas for the past few years. Friday is ready for a new home who has patience and lots of affection for him! He’s ready for Colorado adventures and walks, but Friday’s down to just hangout too. He is completely vaccinated, neutered, and microchipped. His adoption fee is $250. 

Go to our website https://redfernanimalrescue.org/ and FILL OUT AN APPLICATION if you are interested! Due to the amount of inquiries we are receiving, we are prioritizing adoption applications at this time. Make sure you’re filling out an adoption application on Red Fern Animal Rescue’s site in Colorado, as we are not a shelter in Tennessee!

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Ernie! I'm a happy go lucky 1 1/2 year old black mouth cur/shepherd mix in search of my furever home!

I came into Harris County animal shelter with extensive injuries and ligature marks around my torso.  The ropes that were tied around me caused shearing injuries to my abdomen. This led to to a degloving injury to the sheath over my penis. Unfortunately my penis could not be saved after multiple attempts.  I had a P-U procedure performed and my penis was amputated.  Don't let that fool you, I urinate just fine!  The vet has cleared me medically and the trainers said I am a super sweet, playful, wonderful dog...which means I am ready for my furever home in the PNW!

I'm a younger pup with a lot of energy so I hope my new family is quite active. I'd love to be your adventure buddy! I also love playing with other dogs! I can play a bit rough with the other large dog in my house but also know how to tone it down for the smaller ones. I haven't been around young kids but I may knock them over when I'm excited so older ones are probably best. I also haven't met any kitties so I'm not sure how I'd do! I've been working on my crate training in my foster home and I do best with exercise and calming music.

I'm house broken and will gladly share my food and toys with you! I currently weigh 63lbs and am full grown. I cannot wait to explore the PNW with you!

I am currently being fostered in Houston, Texas as I search for my furever home. Once I find the perfect home, Wag Again will schedule me for transport to the PNW. Transport fees are $200 (this is separate from the adoption fee) as this fee is set by the transport company. All transports are done by ground, because those airplanes can be very scary.

animal.description:
TALLULAH      ** AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION  **

Meet Tallulah, Tally for short. She is the biggest, sweetest chunk of chocolate! This precious girl is about 2 years old and even better than Godiva.... well behaved, happy, loves everybody, wants to please and won't wreck your diet!

Tally has only been in her foster home for a short time. She is getting along beautifully and adjusted to her new environment very quickly. She plays nicely with the male and female Labs in her foster home. Tally is a "full figured" girl, but has a lot of bounce and energy. She weighs 67 pounds, but should probably lose about 5-8 pounds. 

Tally is definitely a "people dog." Tally likes to play with other dogs, but loves to get attention from her people most of all. She is very affectionate and tummy rubs are her favorite! Tally likes to get in the small doggie pool in her foster home. We are not sure what she would do in warmer weather with a big pool. If you have a swimming pool, it will probably need to be fenced separately from the yard. We are looking for a home with a nice sized, private fenced yard for Tally to play. She pulls on the leash, so someone will need to continue to work with her on leash manners. 

Tally will fit best with a pretty active family who will take her for walks, play with her and teach her to walk nicely on the leash. She would be a good companion to kids at least 10 years old, due to her size and energy level. 

Tally is spayed, healthy, vaccinated and on heartworm prevention. She is house trained, crate trained (though reluctantly) and even ignores cats. In her new home, we think she will be a good girl without being crated. 

If you live in the DFW area and are interested in adopting Tallulah, please see our web site for adoption information and application. Our adoption fee is $295 + sales tax. www.LoneStarLabRescue.org

Whoever said great things come in small packages, clearly hasn’t met George yet! ??

This chunk of hunk is Big George! A Mastiff mix, 5-6 years old and 135 lbs of pure affection!

His looks can be deceiving as while he appears to be a sedentary old man, he’s actually pretty active and loves loves loves to walk. Along with cuddles and belly rubs of course!

Gorgeous George is somewhat set in his ways, and prefers to live a simple and quiet life without the hassle of any other animals. He’s great with kids but due to his size, literally a small pony ?? WAG would recommend older children in the family.

A secure fenced in yard is required for our big boy to get out and explore, enjoy the sunshine and chill with his new forever family.

So, who needs a big dog bear hug?? ???

All of our animals are fully vetted which includes spay/neuter, up to date on vaccines, wormed, heartworm tested and treated if necessary, up to date on flea/tick/heartworm prevention and microchipped) prior to adoption.

animal.description:
Crisp was found on Christmas Eve day running down a busy street. One of DRWB volunteer was on her way to the vet and saw her. She pulled over and was able to rescue her from 3 bigger dogs that were chasing her.

Poor Crisp had a slight bite on her body, nothing critical, but was taken to the vet right away.  She was loving to her rescuer from minute number 1. She got a bath when she got to her foster's home and she was so happy, she looked content and confident. She didn't have an ID tag or was microchipped, so her family couldn't be located despite efforts to find them.

Blood work came out normal, 4DX Snap test came out negative, she got her teeth cleaned, a few days later she got fixed. She is  8 pounds.

This girl is healthy and happy, she is not hyper and more like low to medium energy, but she can run!

She sleeps in a playpen in a cozy bed and does not like to be bothered. The foster puts a pee pee pad in the playpen in case she wants to go, and she uses it if needed.

She would do best in a calm environment, another adult or senior dog would be great for her, or she could also be the queen of the house.

She is sweet and loving, loves people. We hope to find a loving and forever family for this sweet girl.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Meet Mac! Mac is 4 years old. He is a handsome blonde colored lab. Weighing in at a big and healthy 76#, he's a handsome stoic looking dog.

What's so special about Mac? He is as smart as a whip. This dog learns quickly and can implement without incident. Mac knows Stay, come, sit, paw, down, over, sit pretty, up. Mac knows no, stop, easy. He is a joy to have as a walking/hiking/running companion. He is easy on the leash; does best with a harness. Mac can and will go for miles.

Mac is house trained. He is potty trained. He is crate trained.

Mac is good with other dogs. He enjoys having like friends. He is fostered with 2 females and does very, very well with them. He has met and played with male dogs and did well with them. His interaction is great and he learns from their social cues with respect. Interacting with other dogs has been important in integrating Mac and showing him a positive spin on life.

Mac is good with children. The children that Mac has been around are quiet, very kind to animals, know how to do and what not to do when it comes to dogs in general. Mac is big and he gets excited. Little children may be knocked over until a new routine and structure is met. (6 year old boy, 4ft tall, 41# for reference of good size)

Mac needs a fenced yard, that ideally would have a fence taller than 4ft. This is for his safety and is a must.

Ideally, if you are approved for adoption, we ask for understanding that Mac has finally gained confidence in stability. His family decided he had no place with them after 3 years.

If you have a lot of love to show this dog please send in your application. Patience is a virtue you must have and give to Mac. He's a really great dog! You will be lucky to have his love.

animal.description:
Quiet country/suburban home sought for sweet dog!!

Ruggles is a sweet, loving and snuggly dog who was rescued by his current family 2 1/2 years ago when he was 7 months old.

Sadly he and his siblings were transported from GA to RI for big, noisy adoption events in pet stores. Those that weren't adopted were transported back to GA and brought back to RI the following month. Ruggles made that trip four times before his family found him.

That experience combined with unknown trauma prior means that Ruggles is extremely reactive to large truck sounds (think Amazon delivery trucks and back-up beeps) as well as most unfamiliar sounds. He gets extremely anxious and barks if the neighbors close their car door, for example.

He's come a long way. He no longer chews up his bedding in his crate. He's very trainable; he knows sit, down, leave it (we're still working on stay). He accepted our other dog easily when we adopted him in April. They sleep in our bed and on the couch together. 
However, walks in the neighborhood and park are still anxiety-producing for him. Every person he sees makes him very anxious. With COVID, we've not been able to work on that. He has never been aggressive toward anyone, although he has not been around children (the sounds of kids playing make him very anxious).

His current family lives in Providence in a busy section and they along with the vet behaviorist at Tufts Veterinary School have come to the conclusion that this boy needs to live some place away from the city lights and action - his family adores him but they cannot move and know this is what is right for him. Ruggles is always on alert. If a delivery truck is on our block, he'll bolt out of a deep sleep and bark anxiously.

He does enjoy having another dog in his home.. Most important for him is a quiet environment without a lot of outside noise - thinking perhaps no children as they don't mean to be sometimes but we know how it can be. A fenced yard is key for him as well.

His family is in no rush - they want his next home to be the one if it cannot be them.

Name: Ruggles
Breed: Terrier/Crossbreed
Sex: Male
Age: 3 yo
Weight: 28 lbs
Spayed/Neutered: Yes
Vaccinations: Up to date
Heartworm: Negative
Microchipped: Yes

BASED ON OUR OBSERVATIONS:
Good with Children: Good with children, noise would be the factor preventing this.
Good with Dogs: Yes one required in his home.
Good with Cats: No cats

Adoption Fee: $475.00

IMPORTANT INFORMATION:
Interested in a specific dog, please fill out an application if you are interested in a dog. The number of individual inquiries is overwhelming and we are finding it difficult to respond to each one. We cannot guarantee you will receive a timely response.

Paws New England is a rescue, not a shelter, and as such we do not have our dogs housed in one location - they are in foster homes both in New England and in our southern foster homes. If you're interested in a specific dog, please complete a short online application and you will receive a reply within 48 hours so you can ask questions.

At present, if a dog is listed on our website, the dog is considered still available HOWEVER, may have applications that have come in before yours but it's still too early to know if any are a good match; therefore we encourage you to apply.

NOTICE WITH REGARD TO LOCATION OF DOGS: Please note: Paws New England is a foster-based rescue. We do not have a brick and mortar building to house the dogs we rescue. We have found that dogs in foster homes are much more adoptable because they have been observed in a home setting. Dogs listed with Paws New England typically reside in various locations throughout the south (primarily Tennessee, Texas, and Arkansas) and New England (not necessarily in the state of Rhode Island). You will be notified by the adoption coordinator of the location of the dog you are interested in so you have the ability to decide whether to pursue adoption or not.

Dogs transported to New England are done so at a fee of $150.00 paid directly to the transporting company by Paws New England; no additional transport costs are responsibility of adopter. This fee is included in the adoption donation.

Adoption donations cover pre-adoption vet costs (including vaccinations, spay/neuter when age appropriate, and heartworm testing/treatment when necessary), a microchip, and transportation to New England if necessary.

Donations for our young, healthy puppies and dogs support their fellow canines of advanced age or suffering from injuries and abuse whose donations are reduced but whose veterinary costs are typically much higher. We appreciate your understanding that your dog will help others in need.

All known information about the animal is listed above. We do our best to give accurate information, but most of our dogs are rescues and do not come with a known history.

Paws New England abides by the dog importation regulations set forth in the states of MA, CT, NH and RI.

animal.description:
The name is Logan, and I am a fluffy, 50-pound energetic bundle of husky love!
My favorite passtimes include roaming the yard, taking long walks, eating snow, romping with dog friends, riding in the car, pestering my foster mom when she is in a work meeting and I want attention that very second (sometimes I even pop into the Zoom screen to get a collective "Awwww" from her colleagues and students), showing off my sit/shake/lay down skills for yummy treats, and shredding stuffed toys to get the squeaker out.
I am just a year and a half, so I still have some growing up to do and manners to learn, like walking nicely on a leash. I would love to have a human who takes me to obedience classes so we can bond and I can learn those manners. I am eager to please and thrive on attention. Tell me I am beautiful and give me pets, and I will eagerly roll over for belly rubs. I am potty trained, though. Ask my foster mom. She is so proud that she hasn't had to clean up any of my accidents.
I am looking for an active home that will take me for daily walks, and I require a physical fenced-in yard.
Additionally, I would be so thrilled to have a dog friend to play with whose energy matches my own. I find cats fascinating and want to chase them, but given my exurberant play style, a home with cats isn't a good fit for me.
Got kids? I love them! The more humans to play with, the better! But children over 8 will be better suited for my energy level than young ones.
Applicants with husky breed experience will be given priority. My foster mom is also willing to consider homes within 150 miles of Peoria because she wants the absolute best for me.
If you think we're a match, then go ahead and apply! I am eager to meet you!


Our adoption fee is $260 for dogs over 5 months of age and includes all vaccinations, spay/neuter, micro chip implantation and registration/transfer, heartworm test and much more. Puppies up to 5 months of age are $275 and this includes all sets of puppy vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip implantation and registration and more. To adopt, go to www.fosterpetoutreach.org to complete an application.
Please note: Foster Pet Outreach tries to limit our adoptions to an area within approximately 60 miles of Peoria, Illinois.

animal.description:
Daisy is a 10 months old sweet as can be Akbash.  She is an amazingly fast learner, and took only 1 accident in the house to be potty trained at 9 weeks.  She has had 2 months of on location professional training and you would never know she is still a puppy as she is a super chill little lady.  She gets along with other dogs, but prefers to be the pack leader.  May be better as the only dog.   She is an exceptional protector of livestock and prefers to sit outside and keep watch over the horses at her current home.  She is also fearless, as she ran off a lone coyote that ventured too close to her herd.  She is friendly to strangers, but is able to carry herself confidently if she senses danger.  She is eager to please and loves to cubble, but also knows her commands, and when playtime or snuggle time is over.  Daisy is easy to groom, and does not mind having her nails clipped.  Daisy is  being rehomed because of family circumstances, not because of her personality.
She can be food and toy protective at times.

animal.description:
Archie is "Foster to Adopt," as he is still waiting for his neuter.

Archie is a typical high-energy, excitable, goofy Boston Terrier. He LOVES other animals - he has been introduced to large and small dogs, cats, guinea pigs, and chickens at his foster house. He gets especially excited around big dogs, so he does best with dogs that are okay with him being in their face. Archie gives lots of kisses to his friends. That said, he is responsive to being corrected and does eventually learn which animals like him and which don't - he desperately wishes everyone wanted to play with him. Archie has never lived without another dog in the home and we think he would do best in a home with another playful canine companion. When he gets overstimulated/too excited he does have a habit of humping. He will also mark occasionally when he is in a new place or new items are brought into the home. We imagine these behaviors will decrease when he is neutered (scheduled for 2/3/21), but may not go away completely, especially without training. Archie is excellent in the crate and barely ever barks. He loves toys - both bones and stuffies - and shares very well. Aside from the occasional marking, he is reliably potty-trained and regularly "holds it" for an entire workday. Archie walks well on the leash and does well riding in the car. If he is especially excited, he will seat jump in the car, but is quiet and usually settles down pretty quickly. Because Archie is so easily excited and will need someone who can help him regulate that, we are recommending kids ages 10+. Archie has pretty great recall in the yard and in the house, but we do recommend a fenced in yard for exercise and safety reasons.

Age: 1.5 years old

Breed: Boston Terrier

Weight: 20 lbs

Kid-friendly: Yes, ages 10 and older would be best.

Dogs: Yes!

Cats: Yes!

Crate trained: Yes!.

Potty trained: Yes!

Likes: Playing with other dogs, toys, bones, and stuffies!

Adoption fee: $425

If you are interested in fostering, you must fill out a Foster Application here: http://www.greyfacerescue.org/foster

$50 discount for seniors (65+) and veterans. Adoption fees help pay for the dog's veterinary exam, vaccinations (rabies, distemper, and bordetella), HW test, blood panel, a microchip, and spay/neuter if needed and additional health needs specific to each animal.

animal.description:
Gertrude is a sweet, gentle, calm Chi mix who is 10 years old and weighs 10 lbs. She was surrendered to animal control with 7 of her canine companions when their elderly owner was hospitalized and could no longer care for them. The living conditions in her home were not good and she lost hair due to flea dermatitis, but her fleas have been treated, she gets bathed regularly, and her hair is growing back a little more each day! She is a happy, smart, cautious, low energy girl with captivating eyes who loves car rides, has awesome leash manners, and is learning basic commands in her foster home.  She would be fine in a home with older kids and likes other dogs that are low key like her.  Gertrude could live happily in an apartment and does not require a fenced yard.  Her ideal home will be with someone who is home a lot to give her lots of love & attention.  She would most likely find comfort in a home with one or more dogs that are low energy and small like her.  She is housebroken, crate trained, spayed, fully vaccinated & microchipped. 

For more information about Gertrude, please email us at info@barkvilledogrescue.org. If you would like to adopt this sweet girl, please submit an application for her at https://www.barkvilledogrescue.org/applications

*PLEASE NOTE WE ARE LOCATED IN CANADA AND UNABLE TO ADOPT TO ANOTHER COUNTRY.

Hello, my name is Chiron, and I am approximately 4 years old but I was found as a stray so that is just best guess.

I'm a a super sweet boy and if you give me attention I will quickly become attached and be super loyal. I am very smart, one of the volunteers has helped me learn many tricks. I know sit, shake a paw, high five, stay and leave it. I'm a bit stubborn so I do my tricks best when I know there is a food reward and because I love treats it's really easy to train me. I can be weary of new situations and places so I would love to find a quiet home with someone that will be home with me most of the time. I'm not a fan of being in a kennel as it doesn't allow me to stay close to my person. I do much better roaming around the house and I'm not destructive or overly messy. I am good on leash and do enjoy a daily walk or two.

A large fenced back yard where I can roam around or lay and sun myself when it's warm is ideal and of course someone that it home with me a lot.

If you would like to meet Chiron, please fill in an adoption application.

Luke: As a Skywalker, this 10-week old pup from "a galaxy far, far away" is destined for greatness. Luke is an alpha, a true leader of his rebel 7-pack; he is a strong and fearless "Jedi" dog that also has a warm heart and an adorable, playful nature. He is all white with light brown ears. He has a stout build and a beautiful sturdy face. Luke's exuberant personality is a joy and he has a very pleasant demeanor. Luke also loves to cuddle, unless he's off battling the Empire. He wields his lightsaber (or sticks) in his mouth with amazing dexterity and athleticism. Luke is well behaved on a leash and loves exercise, play, and walks, and of course food & treats - making your training easier. He does fine in a kennel, crate, or traveling on a starship. He is familiar with going potty on hardwood pellets, in a litter bin, or outdoors. He is very intelligent, eager to learn new things, and has an adventurous spirit. After a day of Jedi training or battling stormtroopers, he has no problem sleeping through the night. His momma dog Padme (42 lbs) and twin sister Leia [and 5 other Star Wars siblings] have been his life, but now Luke is looking forward to amazing adventures exploring our galaxy. animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Bear was brought in as a stray to a Utah shelter and was found to have foxtails, burrs and a FISH HOOK in his poor right front foot. Typically Bear was scared, but he has always been kind and loving - assumed to be an abandoned working dog.

Several vet appointments and prescriptions have been required so far and it may not be over - the vet has mentioned that the 4th digit on that foot is fractured and may need to be amputated!! As of now the infection seems to finally be under control and we can move forward with the determination of how to treat the toe.

Through all of the treatment and being constantly in pain Bear has been nothing but kind. He welcomes anyone with a wagging tail and a happy Pyr smile. He loves all dogs big and small and all humans as well. He pays no attention to the kennel cats and is a very content boy who tolerates his treatment and just waits for a treat.

We believe him to be around 2 years old and have yet to find any issues with his personality AT ALL.

I love to go for walks, the best part is when I get to roll and play in the snow as you can see in my photos. I still sometimes can pull on my leash but I'm working on it and take corrections well. I do have a small amount of prey drive but nothing that learning the "leave it" command wouldn't help with. I haven't made many friends at the rescue, it's not that I'm really reactive, I'd just rather ignore them and keep to myself.

A large fenced back yard where I can run would be great as we do love to play, and a family to teach me tricks and manners, and to go on adventures with would be a dream. I should be a only pet home.

If you would like to meet Messiah, please fill in an adoption application.

animal.description:
Oliver is a gorgeous, big, dopey, forever-puppy that steals your heart when you meet him. He loves nothing more than getting pets and attention. He is between 1 and 2 years old, around 27kg and looks like a Lab x Black mouth curr mix with a curly tail!

When Oliver arrived at the rescue, he was COVERED in severe mange- his skin was so dry and itchy- and he was very malnourished, skinny and full of parasites, he had marks that looked like someone had burnt him. Oliver had clearly not had an owner for quite some time and really needed our care. Within a few months he has fully recovered and is now experiencing what it's like to be loved and showing us so much love in return. 

This poor boy has had a pretty tough first few years of life, which has left him a little wary of some things, but he is constantly improving. Oliver went to a training centre and came back much more improved, and we continue to work with him on a daily basis. He is an extremely smart boy who wants to please so he responds well to training. Oliver has been in care for over a year, and continues to be overlooked, we are seriously hoping that this boy's perfect family is looking for him as much as he is looking for them.

Oliver's new parents should have dog experience so they can continue helping him be the best boy possible. Oliver likes all our current dogs at the rescue which range from young puppies to calm, older males but sometimes he can be nervous of other dominant males so it may be best if he is the only big male dog in the house. His current favourite friend to play with is a 13 pound terrier named Callie (playing together in the video on his profile). Oliver needs proper intros with dogs to set him up for success, and could live with a dog sibling after proper intros. He would also be completely fine being an only dog as ultimately what he wants the most is his people's attention.

Oliver can sometimes be reactive to dogs on a leash, but when walked by a confident and relaxed person he pretty much minds his own business unless dogs come into his personal bubble. As long as Oliver is given his space and is engaged on his walks, his reacting stays at a minimum and can be quite easily corrected with consistency. Right now his foster who walks him uses the cue “ready” and Oliver knows to turn and look at her for a treat. Anytime Oliver seems to focus on something that he may naturally react to, “ready” is used to break his focus and he responds. Oliver is also told to sit if he becomes too excited and this acts as a restart for him. Oliver's main “triggers” for reaction are things that excite him, such as barking dogs, someone on a bike or a motorcycle, someone running near him etc. When Oliver does get overly excited or instigated he will lunge on leash and may bark but is overall controllable and easy to regain his focus as long as he is consistently trained. He is a big boy and strong so will need a fairly strong handler for the times he may react. For an experienced dog owner who is used to dogs that need a little extra work, Oliver would honestly be a piece of cake

Oliver does like people after proper introductions, and wants all the pets he can get. When someone new comes into his home they are advised to sit and ignore Oliver (maybe offer him some open handed treats), and within a short period of time you will know exactly when Oliver has decided that you are okay in his books as he will simply place his paw right on you to basically tell you “okay I’m ready” 

Oliver's environment here in Puerto Vallarta is extremely different from environments that he would have in BC, and he does not thrive in this type of environment. Here in PV there are many stray dogs or dogs who are allowed off leash on the streets, which can sometimes be unpredictable as dogs may approach us while on a walk, or sometimes even charge at us when walking Oliver which can understandably set him off. This is not something he would be exposed to in the right setting in BC such as neighbourhoods or leashed areas. In the right environment we know that Oliver would absolutely thrive, as who he is now compared to who he was when he first came into care is an entirely different dog.

Oliver does not like children or cats, they are both too unpredictable for him so he would prefer a home without both. 
Oliver's new family will need to continue working with him to ensure he continues doing well as a lack of training could result in Oliver become more reactive and undo all of the amazing progress this wonderful boy has made. In return you will get a gorgeous big boy who loves you and is always pleased to see you.

Oliver's ideal family would be with people who live a pretty chill lifestyle, and who don’t have too many constant changes as he does best with routine. People who can continue to train and work with him to help him continue being the best boy he can be. Oliver will need a yard, and would not be suited for apartment living. Someone with land that Oliver could run around on would be an absolute dream come true for him. He would be happy to have another non-dominant dog friend to play with, preferably female, but would also do well as an only dog. Oliver is truly such a special boy, it's hard to meet Oliver and not have him steal your heart. He deserves to have a home and a family of his own, and deserves to be in an environment that he can thrive in. 

Oliver has a flight opportunity into BC in the coming months which may be his only chance out for a while with covid travel restrictions. We are really hoping that we can find this wonderful boy a family so that he can be on his way to his new life in his new country when the flight comes.

If you think this sweet boy could be a match for you then you can reply to this posting with some info on yourself/ your family and home dynamic so we can see if we think you could be a match

animal.description:
Hi! It's me Canela and I'm ready to find my forever home! I've been dreaming of a nice cozy warm bed and a forever family for many years. People tell me that I'm a good girl and they have been actively sharing my information/pictures to find my peeps. My ideal companion is someone who will love me unconditionally and be able to give me time to adjust to my new environment. I'm looking for someone who has a zest for life by taking long walks/hikes and also someone to chill with - lounging around the house watching Netflix. I enjoy running around the yard doing bunny hops, belly rubs, going for car rides, baths, napping in my crate and just hanging out with my human. I'm good in my crate, walk great on leash, obedient to my handler and know my basic commands. I've been on several walks (on leash) with large and small dogs, my handlers said I did a good job. However, since I've been living in a kennel at the shelter for so many years I'm under socialized and haven't been given the tools I need to play with dogs off leash. Therefore, it would be best that I am the only animal in my new home at this time. I'm very friendly and absolutely love human attention. My heart has been broken but I'm ready to give my person(s) all my love, companionship, loyalty and best of all ME!

For more information or if you'd like to meet me, please contact Ronda at: bigdogronda@gmail.com

These dogs are looking for homes through private parties in the Los Angeles CA area. This page is a service to help individuals in the L.A. area trying to place dogs into loving homes. The dogs listed on this page are not affiliated with Karma Rescue. We have not evaluated the dogs and they are not under our care. We are not responsible for any adoptions through private parties. To obtain more information about any of these pets, please use the contact information given with each pet's description. All dogs are spayed/neutered prior to being listed on this page.

I am new to rescue, please check back for updates as my foster family gets to know me. You can also watch for stories, pictures and videos about me on our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/groups/40103261297/ Ask to meet me today!!
 
Adoption fee: $475
 
Adoption fees for all dogs/puppies include a $50 refundable training deposit. Complete your basic training program and provide a copy of the certificate within 4 months (120 days) of adoption and we will refund $50 of the original adoption fee.
 
All dogs/puppies have been fully vetted including spay/neuter, micro-chipping, worming, heartworm testing and preventative treatment, flea/tick preventative, and all required age appropriate vaccinations. As required by Wisconsin Act 90, all dogs will have received a veterinarian exam (CVI) within the past 30 days.
 
Our adoption process requires the submission of an application. Applications and Adoption Rules can be found on our website, on the "HOW TO ADOPT" tab at JRsPupsNStuff.org. Upon receipt of the completed application, we will process the application including: contact with your veterinarian and completion of a home visit. Please be sure to include the contact information for your vet as we will call. If your vet requires an information release, please be sure to contact them as soon as you submit your application. We are a group of volunteers with families and jobs, so please be patient and allow a few days for our response.
 
JR's Pups-N-Stuff Dog Sellers License 270089-DS

animal.description:
*PLEASE NOTE: ADOPTERS INTERESTED IN APOLLO MUST HAVE DOG EXPERIENCE & NO YOUNG CHILDREN*

Apollo's story will break your heart. He was seized as part of a serious cruelty case and was starved beyond belief. This poor baby was literally skin and bones when he was rescued, it was difficult to witness. Over the last several weeks he has been in a loving foster home and has doubled in size. He is a 3.5 month old neutered male pit bull terrier mix who weighs 15 lbs. Because of his difficult past, Apollo will need an experienced family without young kids to help provide him with the positive guidance and confidence he needs. He is a bit protective of his food when other dogs are around, but who could blame him after being starved for most of his life? His foster has already started helping him realize he'll have a never-ending supply of food for the rest of his life. Otherwise, he has been great with other dogs and loves to play and hang out with his doggie buddies. Cats are a "no" for him, unfortunately. Apollo is an absolute love bug and incredibly handsome. He'll win you over instantly with his adorable eye patch and pink nose. We cannot wait to see this boy continue to thrive in his forever home. Please help us find Apollo the forever family he so desperately deserves!

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/
We are a foster based organization, so we do not have a facility to visit. Please read our FAQs to learn more: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/faq
Follow us on Facebook for foster updates and a full list of our adoptable pets: https://www.facebook.com/all4pawsrescue/

animal.description:
Lovable and beautiful, Ashley is an adoring family dog looking for her forever home. Ashley was picked up as a pregnant stray on the streets of Arkansas. She gave birth to 6 gorgeous puppies on November 23, 2020. Now that her pups are gone, she is looking for a new family to call her own. Her body is still bouncing back from pregnancy but don’t fret, she is in the process of getting back to her petite and muscular physique. She loves children and other dogs, she’s very playful! We are assuming she gets along well with cats as well, due to her friendly personality. She weighs about 50 pounds and is guessed to be close to 2 years old. She is potty trained and does well in a crate, although not completely necessary if you leave chew toys out for her to play with. She knows basic commands like sit, stay, and will shake your hand all day for treats. She is looking for a forever home, with loving laps to lay on, and a warm bed to snuggle her humans at night.

Our adoption fee is $260 for dogs over 5 months of age and includes all vaccinations, spay/neuter, micro chip implantation and registration/transfer, heartworm test and much more. Puppies up to 5 months of age are $275 and this includes all sets of puppy vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip implantation and registration and more. To adopt, go to www.fosterpetoutreach.org to complete an application.
Please note: Foster Pet Outreach tries to limit our adoptions to an area within approximately 60 miles of Peoria, Illinois.

ALL PETS AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION ONLY TO RESIDENTS OF THE DALLAS/FT WORTH METROPLEX

MEET AND GREET APPOINTMENTS SET UP WITH PRE-APPROVED APPLICATION ONLY

Like all puppies, Foxy needs an adopter who is willing to train and work with her to help her be the best dog she can be.

animal.description:
Personality: Louis is a very energetic, strong, playful dog that is waiting for his forever home! He is very enthusiastic and often jumps in excitement. He is still learning his manners but is very smart and already knows sit, down, and shake. Louis does best with experienced handlers who know how to calm him and redirect him to polite behaviors. Louis also loves to go on long runs, play fetch as long as possible, and even go on hikes to help burn his energy. With his energy, he would benefit from plenty of physical and mental exercise, and an experienced family who is comfortable managing high energy, large dogs. 

History: Came to us as a stray.

Dog/Cat Skills: Louis has participated in playgroup with female and male dogs. He is very forward, rowdy, and playful. He engages in lots of physical contact play and chase. He does try to mount at times, and does not always listen to corrections. He does best with very tolerant, social dogs that can handle his rough and tumble play style and high energy. He can also be tolerant of other rowdy, vocal players. Louis has no known history with cats.

Leash Skills: Louis is a strong dog, and pulls a lot while walking on a leash. He would benefit from the use of a front clipping harness. It also helps when he gets proper outlets for his energy. 

 Primary Color: Black Secondary Color: White Weight: 71.2lbs Age: 1yrs 0mths 1wks Animal has been Neutered

animal.description:
This little darling Princess Piglet has been through a lot. Given up by her family because they didn't have time, she would up in the city shelter. Sadly she was grossly neglected in that home (she was suffering from a severe skin condition, had distended nipples from overbreeding and had a very serious uterine infection that could have been fatal if we didn't treat it immediately) so it was for the best.

Despite all that, Princess Piglet (we call her that because of the adorable snorting noises she makes) is the sweetest, most loving dog you could meet. She loves everyone she meets (kids, strangers, other dogs) and she greets them with a waggy tail and a big smile. And boy does she adores her people often following them around to see what's going on. And she can't get enough cuddles loving to snuggle up while you are watching TV or reading. She is truly one of the most gentle, loving dogs you could meet.

Princess does have some moderate special needs. At 8 years old, she has moderate visual impairment some mild arthritis. She gets around quite well but a home without stairs would be ideal. Otherwise, she is the most wonderful companion anyone could ask for. She makes a great family dog because of her incredible demeanor.  How about considering giving this deserving gal a home for her golden years?
animal.name: Princess Piglet

animal.description:
We just love our hounds here at the funny farm. They tend to have the sweetest dispositions with a love for their other four-legged friends, and kindness towards people. Miss Mavis is no exception! Curious, attentive, affectionate, and bursting with energy, this tri-colored hound to Saving Grace is just shy of a year old. Nose-to-the-ground with a love for her human pals, Mavis ensures to greet each volunteer with a happy wagging tail and soaks up any scratches under her chin or behind the ears that they dole out. She is great in the car and loves all kinds of toys

... furry, squeaky, chew toys and bones!

Mavis is extremely food motivated, and while she is in need of some formal training, she is quick to respond to commands or corrections at the offer of a treat! She is a social butterfly and would love to join you on any dog-friendly outings and will be sure to make quick friends with everyone in the neighborhood! Mavis is a sweet pup who will be a wonderful addition to some lucky family. She is also happy to share her home with a feline friend. Could she be the girl you've been looking for?!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
Pepper Potts is a sweet & loving Lab/Pittie mix who is 2 years old and weighs 50 lbs.  She is a friendly, silly, calm girl who is good with kids, cats, and other dogs.  Pepper came to BarkVille after being seized by Animal Control from a hoarding situation with 36 other dogs.  She is shy with new people, but is very gentle & submissive with other dogs.  She is a medium energy dog with awesome leash manners who likes everyone and is currently learning basic commands in her foster home.  Her foster mom says that Pepper is an amazing dog with a heart of gold who has been through a lot and deserves a change to have a family of her own.  She is looking for a home with another dog and a person/family who will give her the time & space she needs to get comfortable in a new environment.  She is housebroken, crate trained, spayed, fully vaccinated & microchipped.  She is HW+ and is currently available for a foster to adopt situation until her HW treatment is complete and she is medically cleared for adoption. If you are not familiar with Heartworm disease, dogs get it from mosquitos and it is not contagious. It is easily prevented and highly treatable, but requires extended rest during treatment.

For more information about Pepper, please email us at info@barkvilledogrescue.org. If you would like to adopt this sweet girl, please submit an application for her at https://www.barkvilledogrescue.org/applications

Badger is the truest you'll get the Australian Cattle Dog breed! He represents the breed very well. And, because of this, he can be fairly nippy, never out of aggression, just playful! If you are interesting in meeting Badger, please fill out an application on our website FIRST, once approved we will reach out and set up a meet and greet.

animal.description: Um can we say "ears"??? No body shaming though, we promise...they're adorable! ? Luna is a short and squatty 4 year old spitfire Staffy. Though she has the energy of a 4 month old puppy, she has the smarts of an adult which makes her the best of both worlds. People looking at our "Stone Sour puppies" would be wise to give this girl a look too! She adores every single person she's ever met, though she needs practice on not jumping and mouthing when first greeting them because people are her FAVORITE thing in the whole wide world. Cats however she needs to not live with and, though she really likes to play with other dogs, the other would need to be submissive and let her be the rough and tumble pants-wearer in the relationship. A hiker, biker, runner, etc. would find in Luna the perfect athletic partner! She is spayed, up to date on vaccines, dewormed, flea treated, and microchipped, and we ask for people to donate $150-$200 to offset vet costs. She keeps her kennel clean and is working on her leash manners, and thankfully she's very smart and learning quickly! animal.description:
CORA, Belgian Malinois (Shepard) mix
Female, 8 years old, 45 lbs
 
 Cora is a happy, sweet and affectionate girl who arrived PARS from the Cayman Islands in November 2020. Cora was 
  once a family pet but when her owner passed away she was left outside and ignored. When she was first rescued she was emaciated, riddled with fleas and in bad shape.
This mature lady is energetic 
  for her age. She loves her walks and chasing squirrels.   Cora could 
  benefit from training on leash manners as she pulls  and bark at the dogs on her walks..  Ideally Cora would be the only dog in the house. Due to her love of he chase, she should not live with  cats.
Cora is very well-behaved  and calm at home. She`s is fully housetrained.  
  She  is quiet in the house unless she hears a strange noise outside. When 
  she`s left alone  she tends to sleep on the couch or her bed, look out 
  the window, or just nap. She does not beg at the table and takes food and treats gently. She is not at all destructive and only chews on her 
  toys.   Cora loves pets, scratches and above all else her sleep!  
  Her forever home should be an adult only home with no kids and other pets, and  a fenced yard with enough space for her to run and explore.  ADOPTION FEE: $399.

Please download adoption application form at: 
https://www.peelanimalrescuesociety.com/adopt-our-dogs

Fill the form and email to:
info@peelanimalrescuesociety.com
Then we could proceed.

animal.description: Helga is looking for a home with Hilda. We're not sure if they're mother/daughter, sisters, or just plain ol' BFFs, but they definitely belong together. Helga is very nervous with new people, but her curiosity and desire to be loved get the best of her. Her tail gives her away - the more you speak to her in a sing-songy voice, the more it wags and the closer she inches to you. Once you're friends, she shows what a sweet lady she truly is, often sneaking in kisses while you scratch her chest. Together with Hilda, Helga is a lot more confident and playful. They chase each other and explore everything as a pair, always making sure the other is near by. Once you gain their trust, they even try to fit on your lap at the same time. Helga and Hilda are looking for a quiet but active family. They will need to be the only dogs and with children over 12. They need a house with a fenced yard (preferably a privacy fence), so no apartment life for this duo. Do you have space in your home and your heart for two bashful ladies? Come meet Helga and Hilda! Helga and Hilda are Diamond Dogs and will be shown by appointment only. Diamond Dogs are dogs that are currently receiving special training from staff and volunteers through our behavior modification program. If you are interested in learning more about this animal, please fill out an application by clicking here . Be sure to include Helga and Hilda when filling out the survey. After reviewing your application, we will only be reaching out to you if the animal is a good fit for your home.

animal.description: Rocky is a handsome 1-year-old mixed-breed fellow who currently weighs about 39 pounds. He came to SFAS when his guardian could no longer care for him and he is now ready for a new family. Here at the shelter, Rocky has enjoyed playing with his dog friends and meeting new people. Rockys adoption fee is $180 and is a SHELTER HERO!. He is neutered and microchipped and has age-appropriate vaccinations. A licensing/microchip fee may apply. To meet Rocky or to be added to his waitlist, call (505) 983-4309 x 1610 and leave a voicemail message that includes the DOGS NAME, plus YOUR NAME and A PHONE NUMBER - OR e-mail this information to adoption@sfhumanesociety.org. A scheduler will call you back within 48 hours to confirm your request. If you have other dogs at home, tell the scheduler you would like to bring them along for a Meet n' Greet. SFAS offers a variety of excellent training classes, seminars and Trainer Talks led by animal behavior professionals. These are $50 off for animals adopted from any shelter or rescue group! Due to current COVID-19 restrictions, classes and talks are all presented virtually using Zoom. For course descriptions, schedules and registration, visit https://sfhumanesociety.org/our-programs/behavior-training/group-training-classes/ for classes and https://sfhumanesociety.org/our-programs/behavior-training/special-seminars-and-workshops/ for seminars and Trainer Talks.

animal.description:
PLEASE FILL OUT AN APPLICATION FOR ADOPTION! Please do not call the shelter, until you have completed an application and are ready to make an apt for a meet and greet. Inquiries will not be answered at this time.

Fester came to us as an owner surrender.  Fester and his friend Morticia have spent 8 years on chains outside and FINALLY were able to be let off!  Fester has not had an easy life, he has battled wounds, cold, infections and that's just the tip of the iceberg.  He enjoys the company of some female dogs. NO male dogs at all in his home.  He also would not do good with a cat in his home.  Fester is a sweet boy that is learning how much he enjoys his butt being scratched  and he really loves warm blankies inside!  He foes take treats very roughly so watch those fingers!  Older kids are probably best in the household for this reason.  12+ please.  He is ready to start a new life with true love.  Can you provide Fester Adams a good home with A LOT of love?  He will need a dental very soon is his future.  We can not get him in for a dental for months so please understand that is a requirement to adopt him and THE ADOPTER WILL BE RESPONSIBLE FOR PAYING FOR HIS DENTAL. We don't feel it's fair for him to sit here for months waiting on a dental when he could find a home that can provide for him. Fester Adams can also climb chain link fences so PLEASE have adequate fencing.   Please research POSITIVE training techniques before applying to adopt. We care very much about your application answers and they are reviewed for completeness and the best match. Please fill out an application on the included link: https://threerivershs.org/adoption-app-2/

The adoption fee of $200 includes spay/neuter, current vaccines, microchip, free vet visit, 30 days of pet health insurance, puppy book, and engraved ID tag.

animal.description:

They have now been rescued by 11th Hour Rescue & are looking to find a home as a bonded pair as they've spent their lives together. At the shelter they are in a wire crate, snuggled together. They are sweet but a little scared at finding themselves abandoned. :(

Both Chihuahuas are female. Salt, the white one, seems to be a little older at around 6 years of age. Pepper with the beautiful brindle coloring appears to be a little younger, maybe 5-6 years of age. They are very sweet and are going to be wonderful companions for whoever adopts them & gives them a loving home (and lap!)

If you have a place in your heart for this adorable pair, please complete an adoption application at www.ehrdogs.org and mention their names, SALT & PEPPER SCAS!

animal.description: Hi, my name is Troi. I am perhaps the happiest girl in all the land. Everyone would like to be my friend and I will always make time for a romp in the back yard with all my doggie friends. I came to rescue in rough shape, my foster mom said I had the mange. I do not know what that is, but boy an I glad to be better (I was real itchy). My mom says I am easy to teach and i am a good listener, I think she is a sucker for my big brown eyes and waggy tail. Don't tell the other fosters but foster mom buys me t-shirts to wear. She said it is for my skin, but I know it is because I am her favorite. i even have an AC/DC swearshirt, how cool is that? Anyway, I can't wait to have a family of my own, I would LOVE a doggie friend to play with and someone to take me on lots of adventures. I am a good girl, I am learning to walk next to you on a leash and i try really hard not to potty in the house.

animal.description:
Betty is approximately 3 years old. She is potty trained and crate trained. She has pretty good manners too. She is very smart and learns routine quickly. Betty loves to be pet and gets along well with other dogs. Cats are a maybe.. Betty has a high prey drive and cats are similar to the bunnies and squirrels she often likes to chase.. Betty gets along with almost everyone but its probably best that she goes to a home with kids at least 5 or older.

Betty's biggest challenge is her weight. We don't really know her back story but Betty is quite overweight. She has had puppies which may have contributed to her weight but a potential adopter must be committed to her weight loss journey with high protein foods and lots of exercise so we can get Betty to her best healthy weight so she can live a full and active life.

Betty is scheduled for spay surgery February 17th.

For more information, or to apply for adoption, visit our website at: www.RescueOutreach.com

Please note the following will be performed on all animals prior to adoption:

Microchip

Spay/Neuter (unless medically unable at time of adoption, in which case this will be discussed)

Heartworm Testing (dogs); FELV/FIV TeBettysting (cats)

Age appropriate CORE vaccines. Dhpp, Rabies (if old enough)-dog; CVR, Rabies (if old enough) - cat - WE DO NOT ADMINISTER BORDETELLA unless indicated. PLEASE NOTE- puppies and kittens may need to complete vaccination schedule depending on age at time of adoption. 

Dewormed

All breeds are best guess from veterinarian based on physical exam. All animals come from high kill shelters with poor access to resources. Once they arrive to our rescue they are quarantined for health purposes and spoiled in loving foster homes until their forever home is found! Our organization is operated 100% by volunteers who give their time and love out of the goodness of their hearts.

Information: Abby came to us on a transfer. She is a young, submissive young lady who is very smart. She knows some basic commands and is house trained. She is not tested with cats and does well with other dogs. 

 

We are a foster based rescue based out of Muskegon, MI. We have an application process for adopting our pets. We have an application on our website www.caninesrescue.com. PLEASE DO NOT EMAIL US WITH YOUR APPLICATION INFORMATION. WE REQUIRE YOU FILL OUT THE FORM. We check vet references, backgrounds for abuse or neglect and home ownership or speak to the landlord to verify you are allowed to have a pet. Once the application is received and approved then we will set up a time for you to come and meet our pups that are available. All our dogs are up to date on shots, microchipped, been dewormed at least once, and sterilized. All meet and greets are APPOINTMENT ONLY. We do not have a facility that the public can come and view our pets at.

animal.description: 1220581 - Minni is a 2 year old Chihuahua mix (maybe a Chiweenie as she has a longer body). She was a great mama but now is ready for people of her own to love! She has been around other dogs and overall does fine with them but can be protective of food and bones (especially until she gets to know the other dog well). She has been pretty good with the cat in her foster home but is a little unsure of it still, as long as the cat gives her space she is good. She is quite the cuddler and just wants someone to love. She will find her way under the blankets with you if you let her and will snooze there all night long. She may bark a little at first when there is a stranger entering the home (some of this could be because of her puppies too) but a few treats and she is easily won over. She does okay in the crate, but you have to put her in there. She is mostly potty trained and doesn't have accidents when on a steady schedule (so it may take her a few weeks in her new home to settle in) and walks great on the leash. To adopt Minni please complete an application at www.sloppykisses.org/adoptions!

animal.description:
Let me share a little secret with you about CCR - when we get new dogs in, we give out an informal award in the group to "Dog of the Day"! The Dog of the Day is the dog that stole our hearts the most, and the prize is...being kissed and hugged. If you're wondering who recently won Dog of the Day...it's Mochi! Mochi is Dog of the Day, Dog of the Month, Dog of the Year! He's a gentle, sweet, sad-eyed almost three year old boxer mix with a heart of 24 karat gold. Mochi came to CCR from a shelter in Arkansas where he had been owned and sadly given up to the local shelter through no fault of his own. Mochi is a big boy at 80 pounds, but he's definitely a gentle giant. This sensitive boy love kisses and sweet talk, and he has a sadness to him that really makes you want to wrap him up in a big puppy burrito! Mochi would be a great addition to almost any home - he's good with kids, dogs, and probably even cats! Don't you want an award-winning dog in your home? Bring home a certified Dog of the Day!

To meet Mochi, please submit an application at chicagocaninerescue.org!

At 60 pounds, Bethany is a stocky, wiggly, easygoing lady who loves everyone she meets! We think Bethany will be a great Chicago dog - she likes people and dogs alike, and she has a well-adjusted confidence to her that makes her a great option to introduce to new experiences like the dog park and all sorts of fun stuff. Bethany has a lot of energy and athleticism, so an active home would be perfect for her!

animal.description: At MAMCO we understand that in order to continue rescuing moms and babies, we must stretch our finances as far as we are able. For this reason we use variable adoption pricing. By assigning higher adoption fees to high demand moms and puppies, we are able to rescue more families in need.The money raised through these adoptions acts as a benefactor to moms and puppies in our care who require expensive veterinary treatments, have behavioral issues, or need more time to find a home. We often reduce the adoption fees on these harder-to-place moms and puppies to help them find forever families. Adoption fees vary, but all include spay or neuter, microchip, up to date vaccinations and deworming, rabies vaccine at the time of spay or neuter, and 30 days of pet insurance. We also cover hernia repair and cherry eye repair at the time of spay or neuter. Applications can be filled out at mamcorescue.org.

*Due to concerns surrounding COVID-19, we have reformatted the way that we do adoptions in order to follow social distancing protocols. We are thrilled that so many people want to adopt right now, but we are not equipped to handle the large number of calls, applications, and email inquiries we are receiving. We are no longer answering phone calls and are doing all communications with adopters via email. If you have a dog you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application before sending us emails. You do not need a new application for every dog that you are interested in adopting.

Denali is looking for his forever home

Here's what his foster has to say:

"Denali loves to follow you wherever you go, until you sit down and he sees the opportunity to snuggle on your feet or lap. So if you are looking for a loyal companion, then Denali is your man! His mellow personality, ridiculously soft fur and one floppy ear, makes resisting cuddles impossible. Everyone comments on how handsome he is - he's a real head turner. When he's not flirting with humans or warming your feet, he strolls through the house looking for anything to eat. Apples, carrots, bell pepper...even pickles! If humans can eat it, he will certainly give it a try. He's also very well behaved, and will want to spend time with his family. He is very gentle and sweet with kids and wants ALL the attention. A couple or family without other pets, where he can soak up all your love and affection will be his perfect forever home. Be Denali's hero and he will be yours!"
