animal.description:
Twinkie is an approxmately 12 week old collie mix pup that currently weighs 15 pounds.  He is one of three in the litter.  Twinkie is the biggest cuddler.  He likes to hitchhike on your shoulder like a toddler and he will fall asleep there. 
How very wonderful these three are at being puppies!!  They have the rotation of cuddle, play, eat and sleep down pat.  They are into exactly everything a puppy should want to be into...they know all the ways to get out of the trouble they get into....they clean their bowls....they steal everyone's favorite toys,  but they give them back politely when asked.  They are some type of Collie mix, is my best guess.  They will be large dogs, but not giant dogs and they will all have at least slightly fluffy coats. 

Twinkie is up to date on shots and preventatives and is microchipped.   He will be adopted with a neuter agreement due to his size and age.  Twinkie's adoption fee is $250 plus any additional donation you feel appropriate.  Our adoption fee is set to a level to make adoptions happen.  They do not cover our costs. Thank you for your generosity and interest in our dogs!   

All dogs adopted locally through SGDR receive a free six-week session of obedience classes and a lifetime of behavior support through our Project REWARD program with trainer Charlotte Blake.

You must have an approved application before being able to visit a dog. Visit our website below for an adoption application https://www.snootygiggles.com/dog-application/

If you expect to leave the dog alone for long periods of time, please do not consider adopting a puppy.  Puppies need lots of attention and companionship.  Thanks.

All known information about the animal is listed above. We do our best to give accurate information, but most of our dogs are rescues and do not come with a known history.

I am 2 years old, and l am looking for my forever home.

Adoption Donation: $450

All dogs are microchipped, neutered, current on all vaccines, heartworm tested and started on Tri Heart Plus; Vectra 3D.

All household members and any dogs from the household need to be present at the time of the adoption.

Our website is always kept 100% up to date with who is currently available.  As soon as animals are adopted, they are moved to the Adopted Pets page so if they are still listed on the Adoptable Dogs or Cats page, they are still available. So keep any eye on the site for any animals being added as available for adoption as new animals are added everyday! We would recommend if you haven’t done so already that you submit a general online adoption application with us so it is on file for when you are ready to come out and adopt. The adoption counselors will be able to show you many that would be a good fit for your family. Animal House Shelter can not guarantee breed or breed mix of our adoptable animals. The animals are posted on the website as a breed or breed mix based on their physical characteristics they most resemble. We also can not guarantee the ages of our adoptable animals or how large puppies will be when fully grown.

Please fill out an online adoption application. Visit our 'Adopt' page to view adoption process steps, policies, requirements and FAQ. View our 'Visit' page for hours and directions to our shelter. We look forward to seeing you soon!

animal.description: Eugene here! I just wanted to pop in and share why we'd be perfect together. First of all, look at me, could I be more handsome? We'd look so good together. Secondly, I am full of love, and I don't want to brag, but I've been called a good boy a time or two in my life. I am 5 years young and ready to start a new adventure with you! We can keep each other active and have all sorts of fun. You should come check me out, you won't regret it. Thanks for checking in! Due to the Covid-19 virus pandemic, our offices are operating differently than normal. Please read below for more information: Adoptions: We are open by *scheduled appointment only*. Adoptable pets can be viewed online at petharbor.com. Masks are required to enter the building. Please come prepared with a leash/collar, cat carrier, etc for your appointment. The shelter provides a sample bag of Hill's pet food thanks to their shelter program. To schedule an appointment, first fill out an application at dmcasf.org/adoption-application. Once staff have reviewed your application, we will call you as soon as we are able. Please allow 2-3 additional days to process your application due to limited staff. Missing Pet: If your family is missing a pet, please visit petharbor.com to view the impounded animal's descriptions and photos to confirm if your pet is at the shelter. If you see your pet, please call us at 217-425-4508, you may need to leave a voice mail due to limited staff. You may call to schedule a time to look through our stray area. Field Services: If you feel you have an animal control-related issue that needs to be addressed, please call 217-425-4508 Ext. 4 Mon-Fri from 8a-5p and 217-424-1311 between 5p-8a Mon-Fri and all day Saturday and Sunday. Found a pet: Call us at 217-425-4508 to report a found pet and seek assistance in locating a possible owner. Contact Info: 1. Business Hours Phone Number: (217)425-4508 a. Mon-Fri 8a-5p 2. After Hours Phone Number: (217)424-1311 a. Mon-Fri 5p-8a b. All day/night Saturday and Sunday

animal.description:
Blue is a 7 yr old Ridgeback/Lab Mix

Blue is currently located in South Texas and will be transported to the Pacific Northwest.

Are you looking for a buddy to sit with you while you use the bathroom? Is your room too quiet at night and need to hear snoring to fall asleep? Well then do we have the dog for you! Blue is the sweetest dog ever who loves love! We are not sure of his age, but we believe he is on the older side. He is also one of the LAZIEST dogs I have ever met. He will get bursts of energy where he wants to play but for the most part, he Is happy chilling on the couch or his bed. Even though he is lazy he loves to go for walks, and he will do a happy dance, or his tail will go into helicopter mode when he realizes it’s time for a walk. Blue is a typical male who likes to push his boundaries to see what he can get away with and will need a firm voice in the beginning until he learns who is in charge. Blue is blind in one eye but that doesn’t stop him from catching the majority of food that you throw at him (as long as it’s a good toss).

Our organization only adopts within the United States.

Faith and Hope is a multi-state rescue with locations in Texas, Washington and Oregon. All dogs are rescued from the state of Texas to and transported to our Washington and Oregon locations with placement in their adoptive families. Our $425 adoption fee includes all core vaccinations (DHPP, rabies, spay/neuter, microchip)

If interested in learning more, please email us at faithandhopeadoptions@gmail.com or fill out our online application.

https://www.faithandhopefoundation.org/adoptionapp

If interested in learning more about our adoptable dogs and adoption process, or our foster home program, please contact us at above email.

Due to the number of requests that we receive on our puppies and dogs, please be advised that all adoption applications are processed in the order received. Once we send you an application, your place in line does not get reserved until your application is returned to us.

animal.description:
JENNA
AVAILABLE FOR: Adoption/Foster to Adopt

BORN: December 2017

SEX: Female

BREED: Basenji/Boxer Mix

WEIGHT: 37 lbs.

MARL ARRIVAL: Jenna was transferred to MARL from another facility.

BACKGROUND: Meet Jenna! If there is a phrase that describes Jenna fully, that phrase would be "center of attention!" Jenna absolutely loves every single person she meets, and is happiest when she's included in anything and everything you're doing. A social butterfly, she greets everyone with hugs and kisses, and is sure to brighten up your life in these dark times. If you've been searching for a friend to get you through quarantine, then look no further because Jenna is the one for you!

COMPATIBILITY: Based on our evaluation, we feel that Jenna would do best as the only animal.

MEDICAL NEEDS: Jenna had luxating patella corrective surgery, and is currently recovering. Jenna will need to be kept on exercise restriction until cleared by MARL medical staff. If you have questions about Jenna or her medical treatment, please give our front office a call at 248-335-9290.

animal.description:
Blue is a 7 yr old Ridgeback/Lab Mix

Blue is currently located in South Texas and will be transported to the Pacific Northwest.

Are you looking for a buddy to sit with you while you use the bathroom? Is your room too quiet at night and need to hear snoring to fall asleep? Well then do we have the dog for you! Blue is the sweetest dog ever who loves love! We are not sure of his age, but we believe he is on the older side. He is also one of the LAZIEST dogs I have ever met. He will get bursts of energy where he wants to play but for the most part, he Is happy chilling on the couch or his bed. Even though he is lazy he loves to go for walks, and he will do a happy dance, or his tail will go into helicopter mode when he realizes it’s time for a walk. Blue is a typical male who likes to push his boundaries to see what he can get away with and will need a firm voice in the beginning until he learns who is in charge. Blue is blind in one eye but that doesn’t stop him from catching the majority of food that you throw at him (as long as it’s a good toss).

Our organization only adopts within the United States.

Faith and Hope is a multi-state rescue with locations in Texas, Washington and Oregon. All dogs are rescued from the state of Texas to and transported to our Washington and Oregon locations with placement in their adoptive families. Our $425 adoption fee includes all core vaccinations (DHPP, rabies, spay/neuter, microchip)

If interested in learning more, please email us at faithandhopeadoptions@gmail.com or fill out our online application.

https://www.faithandhopefoundation.org/adoptionapp

If interested in learning more about our adoptable dogs and adoption process, or our foster home program, please contact us at above email.

Due to the number of requests that we receive on our puppies and dogs, please be advised that all adoption applications are processed in the order received. Once we send you an application, your place in line does not get reserved until your application is returned to us.

animal.description:
MEET BUSTER!!

Underdog Rescue does not physically have this dog in its possession. He is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A4465702.

Buster is a big, beautiful boy that has been at the shelter for way too long now. He's been there for more than 60 days and he wants to go home soon. All of the volunteers that have taken Buster for a walk have all stated he is such a pleasure to walk. He walks easily on the leash and just loves to smell and take in all of his surroundings. He checks in often to make sure everything is okay. He will "sit" on command for a treat and takes them gently. Buster loves treats! He's also non-reactive to all of the barking dogs in their kennels when he gets out for a walk. He enjoys going to the play yard and will play with toys for a while but what he really loves is if you sit on a chair so he can put his head in your lap and get petted. He will also roll over so he can get some pets on his belly too.

Buster can be more timid around men but he did well in a home with a 14 year old and the shelter recommends he go to a home with older children. He did get overwhelmed when taken to the play yard with other dogs so he might do well with a companion that is calm and laid back like he is. If you think Buster could be a good fit in your home, please come and meet him today! Please bring any dogs you may already have at home to meet him to make sure it will be a good fit.

If you are interested in saving this pet, please reach out via this link: https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/foster/BPAZ/Dog

To actually visit with this pup, please make an appointment here: https://mcaccappointments.as.me/adopt. NOTE: People who sign up for these appointments often no-show, and we have seen that you can generally show up and let them know you are there to meet this particular dog and the shelter will squeeze you in, except from 12-3PM or closer to the 6PM closing time. (Please know this is not a guarantee). If the dog is at risk, please ask for a supervisor to meet that particular dog.

*Please Note: This animal is courtesy posted for the Maricopa County Shelter; UNDERDOG RESCUE DOES NOT HAVE THIS DOG. MCACC is located at 2500 S. 27th Avenue, Phoenix. Different adoption fees/policy may apply. Please visit MCACC's website http://www.maricopa.gov/pets/locations.aspx for hours. You may also wish to call 602-506-7387 (PETS) and provide the animal's A# above to verify is still available.

Hi my name is Cody! I’m 13 years old and 20 lbs! I’m good with other dogs, cats, and kids. My owner fell ill and is unable to take care of me. I went straight into foster care and have adjusted myself quite well. Don’t let my age fool you; I’m a spry guy! I can jump up and down onto the couch, go up and down the stairs, and even get up onto the headrest of couches with ease! I’m a fun guy and enjoy hanging beside you and observing.

You can still come adopt me or even join our foster program to help the humans learn all the awesome things about new dogs like me! Learn more on our website! 

Hope to see you soon! 

What breed am I? Mixed mutt! ODHS does not breed label (unless there’s official paperwork), as studies show it is nearly impossible to tell the exact breed of each dog based off of their appearance.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Please contact EF for more information about this pet.Thanks for your interest in a pet from A.R.F.! If you see a pet here, they are still available for adoption and you should apply through our adoption application on our website at https://www.arf-il.org/adopt/application/
Cookie is a 5 year old female Shepherd Mix who weighs in at 40 pounds. She is good with other dogs, however, will do best if fed separately as she likes to keep the food to herself. Her foster thinks she would do ok with cats too, but does not have any cats in the home. Cookie is a very nice girl! Her foster describes her as laid back, friendly, and calm. She can, however, be a little clumsy and given her strength, she may do better with children age 8 and up.

Cookie is micro-chipped, up to date on all vaccinations, housebroken and spayed. Her new family will be required to complete a basic obedience course of their choosing.

Cookie's adoption fee is $300. A meeting will not be scheduled until you have an approved application, so if you're interested in adopting Cookie fill out an Online Application today!

Once your application has been approved, an ARF volunteer will contact you to arrange a meeting.

Thank you for considering a rescue pet from A.R.F.-Animal Rescue Foundation! We are
based in Wheaton, IL and conduct adoption events in the DuPage County area. If you are interested in adopting one of our pets, please submit an adoption application at https://www.arf-il.org/adopt/application/

Adoption appointments are scheduled based on the order of applications received, so submit your application early! Submitting an application does not commit you to any animal but does get you a head start with the adoption approval process. Due to a high volume of applications, we are often unable to respond to questions or schedule meetings until your application has been approved. More information about our adoption process can be found on our website here: https://www.arf-il.org/adopt/

As an all-volunteer, foster home-based organization, A.R.F. Animal Rescue Foundation does not have a facility where applicants can visit our animals. Please visit https://www.arf-il.org/events/ for a list of our upcoming adoption events.

Thank you for choosing to adopt, not shop!

animal.description:
Ella is a 45 lb 1.5 yr old Staffordshire Terrier Mix

Ella is currently located in South Texas and will be transported to the Pacific Northwest.

Ella is a super sweet loving pup with lots of energy. She loves to go for walks, and is learning not to pull. She knows the sit command and is working on stay. She would flourish with a little training. Ella loves puppies and she’s great with my older dogs and loves to play. She’s a great dog. She loves to have belly rubbed. Ella thinks she is a lap dog. She loves to be picked up and held. She is house trained, and kennel trained. Ella eats in her kennel. She stays in her kennel when I leave the house because I have too many to leave unsupervised. She gets in her kennel around 7pm with a treat then lights out. She gets up and goes straight outside between 6:30-7:00am. No kennel accidents. She’s really a wonderful pup. Very sweet and loving. She likes to lay beside you and get some love while you watch tv. She never meets a stranger and loves kids. She’s a beautiful, sweet pup and she will make a great addition to any family.

Kit and Dottie (sisters named after the sisters in A League of Their Own) arrived together from the Bissell Pet Foundation in St. Landry, Louisiana.  These girls have been thru thick and thin together but we have decided they will do best in separate homes, they love each other but rely too heavily on each other.  They are both very loving and super affectionate.  They walk like angels on a leash and are up for all of the adventures life has to offer.  We would love to adopt them separately but in close proximity so allow for play dates with each other.   

Kit is currently finishing up heartworm treatment (covered by the rescue) and is spayed and up to date on her vaccines.

Apply to adopt this cuddle bug today! She is so looking forward to calling your home her furever after.

www.LuckyDogRefuge.com

READ THE FOLLOWING FOR INSTRUCTIONS ON SUBMITTING AN APPLICATION FOR THIS PET:

- The first step towards adoption is to complete an adoption application, which can be found online at our website www.LuckyDogRefuge.com, under the “Apply Now” tab

or

at https://forms.gle/LXKMKSnagxLSad668.

- Do NOT use the Petfinder links or email to ask us about our adoptable dog listings - we do not always receive these messages and will not respond to them.

animal.description:
Ella is a 45 lb 1.5 yr old Staffordshire Terrier Mix

Ella is currently located in South Texas and will be transported to the Pacific Northwest.

Ella is a super sweet loving pup with lots of energy. She loves to go for walks, and is learning not to pull. She knows the sit command and is working on stay. She would flourish with a little training. Ella loves puppies and she’s great with my older dogs and loves to play. She’s a great dog. She loves to have belly rubbed. Ella thinks she is a lap dog. She loves to be picked up and held. She is house trained, and kennel trained. Ella eats in her kennel. She stays in her kennel when I leave the house because I have too many to leave unsupervised. She gets in her kennel around 7pm with a treat then lights out. She gets up and goes straight outside between 6:30-7:00am. No kennel accidents. She’s really a wonderful pup. Very sweet and loving. She likes to lay beside you and get some love while you watch tv. She never meets a stranger and loves kids. She’s a beautiful, sweet pup and she will make a great addition to any family.

Our organization only adopts within the United States.

Faith and Hope is a multi-state rescue with locations in Texas, Washington and Oregon. All dogs are rescued from the state of Texas to and transported to our Washington and Oregon locations with placement in their adoptive families. Our $375 adoption fee includes all core vaccinations (DHPP, rabies, spay/neuter, microchip)

If interested in learning more, please email us at faithandhopeadoptions@gmail.com or fill out our online application.

https://www.faithandhopefoundation.org/adoptionapp

If interested in learning more about our adoptable dogs and adoption process, or our foster home program, please contact us at above email.

Due to the number of requests that we receive on our puppies and dogs, please be advised that all adoption applications are processed in the order received. Once we send you an application, your place in line does not get reserved until your application is returned to us.
